   <info xml:lang="en">
      <p>The Language Archive Cologne (LAC) supports research, learning and teaching with high
         quality and dependable digital language resources. The LAC facilitates free and open online
         access to research data. It does this by preserving digital audio and video data,
         annotations, and other digital language data in the long term, and by promoting and
         disseminating these resources. The LAC promotes open and sustainable practices in the use
         of digital language data in the humanities and provides technical advice to the research
         community, and supports the deployment of digital technologies in research and
         teaching.</p></info>
